Description: Brand name: RICKENBACKER Series name: RICKENBACKER 400 SERIESDate of manufacture: 1956 Rickenbacker made the Combo 400 model from 1956 until 1958. This one was made in 1956, and was the first Rickenbacker guitar with a tulip-shaped body, and also the first featuring neck-through-body construction. The Combo 400 has a single pickup, set into a recessed cavity in at the neck end of the body. The pickguard is gold anodized aluminum. Finish is green. I had this guitar autographed by: Greg Lake (from Emerson Lake & Palmer), Ian Hunter (Mott the Hoople), Roger Hodgson (Supertramp), and Howard Jones. They were a touring with Ringo Star & The All Star Band, at my music venue The Norva, located in Norfolk, Virginia (around 2001-2002). Definitely one of a kind guitar. Serial number 4C665.
